# Project Conventions

This project uses scoped instruction files. Read the relevant one before working on code in that area.

## Instruction Files

| Scope | File | Applies to |
|---|---|---|
| Project-wide | `.github/copilot-instructions.md` | Stack, directory layout, file map, principles, workflow |
| Python | `.github/python.instructions.md` | `backend/**/*.py` — type hints, DB schema, API routes, testing rules |
| TypeScript | `.github/typescript.instructions.md` | `frontend/src/**` — module responsibilities, import graph, UI conventions |

## When to read what

- **Starting a new task?** → Read `.github/copilot-instructions.md` first for project context.
- **Editing Python?** → Read `.github/python.instructions.md` for conventions.
- **Editing TypeScript?** → Read `.github/typescript.instructions.md` for conventions.
- **Changing DB schema or API?** → Both `copilot-instructions.md` (ripple-effect checklist) and `python.instructions.md` (schema + helpers).

## Quick reference

- Python 3.13 + uv · Flask 3 · pytest · SQLite
- TypeScript 5 (strict) + bun · ESLint 9
- Tests required for every new behavior.
- 400-line soft limit per file.
- Run `uv run python -m pytest -q` after Python changes.
- Run `bun run build && bun run lint` after TypeScript changes.